Policemen patrolling Bugaje to the Jibia route in Katsina State have intercepted three suspected bandits and a supplier of an injection allegedly used to induce violence in the criminals, making them inhuman and wild. This was disclosed by the Police Public Relations Officer in the state, SP Gambo Isah, while briefing newsmen on the recent achievement of the command on Monday. Speaking at the command headquarters, Isah said while conducting a search on the hoodlums, who were riding on two brand new motorcycles, Haojue and Honda CG (aka Boko Haram), 2,400 bottles of Pentazocine injection were found in their possession. He added that the suspects confessed that they were supplying the items to bandits in Dunburum Forest in Zamfara State. Among those apprehended include one Yusuf Abubakar from Kano State, who confessed to supplying the injection to the suspects.